tp:treatment-sec.p:
Head
(
Figs 1–3
). Frontal tubercles very small, about 2 μm in diameter (
Fig. 1
). Temporal setae 8–13. Clypeus with 16–21 setae. Antenna with 10 flagellomeres, 806–845 μm long; ultimate flagellomere 312–390 μm (
Fig. 3
). AR 0.82–0.88. Maxillary palpomeres 2–4 combined 380–410 μm long, their individual lengths (in μm): 40–50: 75–85: 100: 165–175 (
Fig. 2
). Antenna length/palp length 2.06–2.19.

Remarks.
When comparing males from different regions of 
East Asia
, slight morphological differences were revealed (see 
Table 2
). Chinese specimens turned out to be slightly larger than the Far Eastern and South Korean ones. In Far Eastern males, the 4th segment of the maxillary palp is much longer than the 3rd, whereas in Chinese and South Korean males, the 3rd and 4th segments are the same length. The AR value ranges from 0.75 (Southern 
Korea
) to 1 (
Chine
).
